<h2 id="427">4/27</h2>
<ul>
  <li>FT‚Äôs writer suggests China to expand its financial influence on the market by expanding its infrastructure and real estate investment. I don‚Äôt think it is a good idea. China already over-invests in those areas. What it should do is to stop pursuing virtual growth by that kind of over-investment, and rather focus on long and sustainable growth. In the near future, China will suffer from population aging and slower growth, thus it should start preparing against those problems.</li>
