<h2 id="429">4/29</h2>
<ul>
  <li>As mentioned in the April 15th post, developing countries would have less severe damage by coronavirus, as they rely less on the service industry. However, recently, the local currency is excessively used for government spending. In a crisis, the exchange rate collapses, and it will lead to losses to foreign investors. This shift in risk is analogous to that of investment banks and private equity.</li>
</ul>

